            <thetext>The default content of the HtmlArea should contain a &lt;P&gt; element with default settings for font-size and font-family. This way it would be possible to offer the user a default setup concerning font settings. The default content should also be set/inserted if an user is completely removing the written content.

Implementing this behaviour would solve following issues:

  * resulting HTML is equipped with &lt;P&gt; element thus leadling to an identical presentation of the written content everywhere (e.g. an external program showing the HTML)
  * every browser (especially Firefox) can handle the content better if a surrounding &lt;P&gt; element is present. This ranges from formatting the content to entering new paragraphs. Many problems during editing can be solved this way.
  
The following parts need to be implemented
  * two new properties for setting a default font family and size
  * sensible default content set whenever &quot;setValue&quot; is used
  * sensible default content set at startup when no content is present and the user navigates (clicks or tabs) into the HtmlArea
  * sensible default content reset whenever the user is removing the whole content</thetext>
          </long_desc>
